# Optimal ranges on based standards
OPTIMAL_RANGES = {
    'temperature': (22, 24), # C - WHO office standard
    'humidity': (40, 60), # % - ASHRAE 55 standard
    'co2': (400, 1000), # ppm = ASHRAE ventilation standard
    'noise': (35, 55), # dB - classroom acoustic standard
    'light': (300, 500) # lux - reading/writing standard
}

print("=== Optimal Environmental Ranges ===\n")
for param, (min_val, max_val) in OPTIMAL_RANGES.items():
    print(f"{param.capitalize()}: {min_val} - {max_val}")

=== Optimal Environmental Ranges ===

Temperature: 22 - 24
Humidity: 40 - 60
Co2: 400 - 1000
Noise: 35 - 55
Light: 300 - 500
In[8]:
def calculate_comfort_score(row):
    """
    Calculate comfort score (0 - 100) based on environmental parameters

    Scoring:
    - Start with 100 points
    - Deduct points for each parameter outside optimal range
    - Deduction proportional to deviation severity
    """
    score = 100

    for param, (min_val, max_val) in OPTIMAL_RANGES.items():
        value = row[param]

        if value < min_val:
            # Below minimum
            deviation = (min_val - value) / min_val
            penalty = min(deviation * 25, 30) # Max 30 points per parameters
            score -= penalty

        elif value > max_val:
            # Above maximum
            deviation = (value - max_val) / max_val
            penalty = min(deviation * 25, 30)
            score -= penalty

    return max(score, 0) # Never go below 0

# Apply to dataset
df['comfort_score'] = df.apply(calculate_comfort_score, axis=1)

print("Comfort scores calculated")
print(f"\nAverage comfort score: {df['comfort_score'].mean():.1f}/100")
print(f"Median comfort score: {df['comfort_score'].median():.1f}/100")
print(f"Min comfort score: {df['comfort_score'].min():.1f}/100")
print(f"Max comfort score: {df['comfort_score'].max():.1f}/100")

def generate_recommendations(row):
    """
    Generate specific actionable recommendations based on parameter values
    """
    recommendations = []

    # Temperature
    if row['temperature'] > 24:
        if row['temperature'] > 27:
            recommendations.append(" URGENT: Lower AC to 22C or open all windows immediately")
        else:
            recommendations.append(" Lower AC temperature by 2C or increase ventilation")

    elif row['temperature'] < 22:
        recommendations.append(" Increase heating or close windows")

    # CO2
    if row['co2'] > 1000:
        if row['co2'] > 1500:
            recommendations.append(" URGENT: Poor air quality - open windows immediatelyand reduce occupancy")
        else:
            recommendations.append(" Increase ventilation - open windows or improve HVAC airflow")

    # Humidity
    if row['humidity'] > 60:
        recommendations.append(" Use dehumidifier or improve air circulation")
    elif row['humidity'] < 40:
        recommendations.append(" Use humidifier or place water containers in room")

    # Noise
    if row['noise'] > 55:
        if row['noise'] > 70:
            recommendations.append(" URGENT: Excessive noise - implement noise control measures")
        else:
            recommendations.append(" Reduce noise sources or add sound dampening materials")

    # Light
    if row['light'] < 300:
        recommendations.append(" Increase lightning - open blinds or add lamps")
    elif row['light'] > 500:
        recommendations.append(" Reduce glare - partially close blinds or adjust lightning")

    return " | ".join(recommendations) if recommendations else "All parameter within optimal range"

# Apply to dataset
df['recommendations'] = df.apply(generate_recommendations, axis=1)

# Show example
print("=== Sample Recommendations ===\n")
print(df[df['comfort_score'] < 70][['timestamp', 'comfort_score', 'recommendations']].head(10))

# Create hour-of-day vs parameter heatmaps
fig, axes = plt.subplots(2, 3, figsize=(18, 10))

parameters = ['temperature', 'humidity', 'co2', 'noise', 'light', 'comfort_score']
titles = ['Avg Temperature by Hour & Day', 'Avg Humidity by Hour & Day', 
          'Avg CO2 by Hour & Day', 'Avg Noise by Hour & Day', 
          'Avg Light by Hour & Day', 'Avg Comfort Score by Hour & Day']

for idx, (param, title) in enumerate(zip(parameters, titles)):
    ax = axes[idx // 3, idx % 3]

    # Pivot table: rows=hour, columns=day
    pivot = df.pivot_table(
        values=param,
        index=df['hour'],
        columns=df['timestamp'].dt.date,
        aggfunc='mean'
    )

    sns.heatmap(pivot, cmap='RdYlGn_r', ax=ax, cbar_kws={'label': param})
    ax.set_title(title, fontweight='bold')
    ax.set_xlabel('Date')
    ax.set_ylabel('Hour of Day')

plt.tight_layout()
plt.savefig('hourly_heatmaps.png', dpi=150, bbox_inches='tight')
plt.show()

print("Hourly pattern heatmaps saved")

# Calculate potential improvement
print("=== Impact Assessment ===\n")

current_avg = df['comfort_score'].mean()
print(f"current average comfort score: {current_avg:.1f}/100")

# Simulate fixing primary issue (High CO2)
df_simulated = df.copy()

# Assume ventilation improvement reduce C02 by 30%
df_simulated['co2'] = df_simulated['co2'] * 0.7

# Recalculate comfort scores
df_simulated['comfort_score_improved'] = df_simulated.apply(calculate_comfort_score, axis=1)

improved_avg = df_simulated['comfort_score_improved'].mean()
improvement = improved_avg - current_avg

print(f"\nProjected Improvement (with 30% CO2 reduction):")
print(f"   New average comfort score: {improved_avg:.1f}/100")
print(f"   Improvement: +{improvement:.1f} points ({(improvement/current_avg)*100:.1f}%)")

# Visualization: Before vs After
fig, axes = plt.subplots(1, 2, figsize=(14, 5))

# Before
axes[0].hist(df['comfort_score'], bins=30, edgecolor='black', alpha=0.7, color='red')
axes[0].axvline(current_avg, color='darkred', linestyle='--', linewidth=2, label=f'Mean: {current_avg:.1f}')
axes[0].set_xlabel('Comfort Score')
axes[0].set_ylabel('Frequency')
axes[0].set_title('Current Conditions', fontweight='bold')
axes[0].legend()
axes[0].grid(True, alpha=0.3)

# After
axes[1].hist(df_simulated['comfort_score_improved'], bins=30, edgecolor='black', alpha=0.7, color='green')
axes[1].axvline(improved_avg, color='darkgreen', linestyle='--', linewidth=2, label=f'Mean: {improved_avg:.1f}')
axes[1].set_xlabel('Comfort Score')
axes[1].set_ylabel('Frequency')
axes[1].set_title('After Ventilation Improvement', fontweight='bold')
axes[1].legend()
axes[1].grid(True, alpha=0.3)

plt.tight_layout()
plt.savefig('improvement_simulation.png', dpi=150, bbox_inches='tight')
plt.show()

print("Improvement simulation saved")
